text.tspan: Switzerland: COVID-19 weekly death rate by vaccination status, All ages
Death rates are calculated as the number of deaths in each group, divided by the total number of people in this
group. This is given per 100,000 people.
Note: Data coverage includes both Switzerland and Liechtenstein. Unvaccinated people have not
received any dose. Partially-vaccinated people are excluded. Fully-vaccinated people have received all
doses prescribed by the initial vaccination protocol. The mortality rate for the 'All ages' group is
age-standardized to account for the different vaccination rates of older and younger people.
Data source: Federal Office of Public Health
